repnme.cdata!: Togo - Second Cocoa - Coffee Development Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The project would continue cocoa-coffee
            rehabilitation begun under the first cocoa-coffee
            development project. It would be implemented over a five and
            a half year period and focus mainly on replanting by about
            17,000 smallholders of 7,500 ha of coffee and 4,000 ha of
            cocoa; foodcrop planting within cocoa and coffee areas as
            well as outside the plantations; providing marketing
            facilities for plantain; supply the farmers with improved
            extension services, including cocoa, coffee and foodcrop
            planting materials; rehabilitation and maintenance of 300 km
            of feeder roads in the project area; and technical
            assistance to carry out a project evaluation, including
            preparation of a possible follow-up project, and to
            strengthen SRCC, the project executing agency and PCU, the
            Project Credit Unit.

repnme.cdata!: Togo - Second Cocoa - Coffee Development Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The Second Cocoa Coffee Development
            Project for Togo will continue cocoa-coffee rehabilitation
            begun under the First Cocoa-Coffee Development Project. It
            will be implemented over a five and a half year period and
            focus mainly on replanting by about 17,000 smallholders of
            7,500 ha of coffee and 4,000 ha of cocoa; food-crop planting
            within cocoa and coffee areas as well as outside the
            plantations; providing marketing facilities for plantain;
            supply the farmers with improved extension services,
            including cocoa, coffee, and food-crop planting materials;
            rehabilitation and maintenance of 300 km of feeder roads in
            the project area; and technical assistance to carry out a
            project evaluation, including preparation of a possible
            follow-up project, and to strengthen SRCC (Societe Nationale
            pour la Renovation et le Developpement de la Cacaoyere et de
            la Cafeiere Togolaises - National Cocoa and Coffee
            Development Agency), the project executing agency and PCU
            (Project Credit Unit).
